Title: Series: Four landscapes with the Holy Family on their Flight into Egypt
Description: The Holy Family near a lake. Landscape with the Virgin holding the swaddled Christ Child as she sits on the ass, Joseph walking behind them at centre right, three cherubs among the three tall trees growing on the mound in left middle distance; from a series of four plates. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of four plates etched and published by Swanevelt (Hollstein 6-9). Drawings for the complete series are in Florence. For a complete set see s.2274-2278; F,2.207; 1844,0425.14-16 and 1868,0822.758. This is proof before lettering, for later state see see S.2274. For a copy see F,2.223.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (6.I)
Acquisition notes: 1844,0425.1 to 27 cost £145 8s 6d in total. Individual prices have been entered when known.
